<title>CHINA: China bank offers 30 bln yuan loan to Three Gorges.</title>
<headline>China bank offers 30 bln yuan loan to Three Gorges.</headline>
<dateline>SHANGHAI 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The China Development Bank, set up to provide funding to major infrastructure projects, has signed a contract to supply 30 billion yuan in loans to the Three Gorges Dam, the Shanghai Securites News said on Monday.</p>
<p>The agreement, signed on Sunday in the central city of Wuhan, said the bank would supply the Yangtze River project with three billion yuan each year from 1994 to 2003 to provide the main financing for the construction of the dam, the paper said.</p>
<p>By the end of September, 9.1 billion yuan in loans had been dispersed by the bank for the project, the newspaper said but gave no further details.</p>
</text>
